              "text": "Fantastic—London is amazing. I can tailor plans once I know a bit more. To start, here’s a quick 5-day starter plan and a few questions.\n\n5-day starter itinerary (classic highlights)\n- Day 1: Westminster area – Westminster Abbey, Parliament/Big Ben, Buckingham Palace, St James’s Park; optional stroll along the Mall.\n- Day 2: The British Museum in Bloomsbury + Covent Garden (street performers, shops) + Leicester Square/Shoreditch by evening.\n- Day 3: South Bank walk – Tate Modern, Shakespeare’s Globe, Borough Market; consider a ride on the London Eye or a Thames cruise.\n- Day 4: Kensington museums or Notting Hill/Portobello Market; Hyde Park/Piccadilly area for evening dining.\n- Day 5: Day trip options (Windsor Castle, Oxford, or Greenwich) or extra time in East London (Spitalfields, Shoreditch, markets).\n\nA few quick questions to tailor it\n- How many days do you have, and when are you traveling?\n- What’s your budget range for accommodation?\n- What are your top interests (history, art, theater, food, markets, parks)?\n- Any must-see items or places to avoid?\n- Where will you be flying into, and how do you plan to get around (Oyster card/Contactless preferred)?\n- Any mobility or accessibility needs?\n\nIf you’d like, I can draft a personalized day-by-day plan with a rough budget and a packing list. I can also fetch current London weather for your dates or help with transport options and theatre tickets. What would you like to do first?",
